  displayName: Tikbalang
  description: Characterized in many stories as horse-headed and human-bodied, the
    tikbalang is a trickster spirit associated with misdirection and confusion. Oral
    traditions often explain lost paths, circular journeys, and sudden disorientation
    through tikbalang influence. Rather than brute predation alone, it is remembered
    for manipulating perception and turning certainty into doubt.
